#: ../../source/api/prepshot._model.heat_rate.rst:2
msgid "heat_rate"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:1
msgid "Piecewise-linear heat rates (convex, no UC required)."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:3
msgid ""
"Standard CEM/PCM addition for thermal generators: their fuel-burn- per-"
"MWh isn't constant across the operating range. Above the design point, "
"marginal heat rate increases (each additional MWh costs more fuel than "
"the previous one). LP-friendly approximation: split the operating range "
"into K segments with monotone-non-decreasing multipliers, force the "
"dispatch to use the cheapest segment first."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:10
msgid ""
"The convexity matters: with non-decreasing multipliers across ascending "
"output ranges, the LP optimum naturally fills segments in order (cheapest"
" first) without any binary ordering constraints. Real heat-rate curves "
"below the design point (where part-load losses dominate) are concave -- "
"those can only be modelled with no- load + startup costs in the UC "
"overlay (v1.15+)."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:18
msgid "Inputs"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:20
msgid ""
"``tech_heat_rate.csv`` (table format) -- one row per (tech, segment), "
"with columns:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:23
msgid "``tech`` -- technology name"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:24
msgid "``segment`` -- integer index (1, 2, 3, ...)"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:25
#, python-format
msgid ""
"``frac_max`` -- cumulative cap fraction at the upper edge of this segment"
" (e.g., 0.5 for segment 1 means \"0-50 % of cap\"). Segments must form a "
"partition: ``frac_max`` strictly increasing, last value = 1.0."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:29
msgid ""
"``multiplier`` -- relative heat rate within this segment, 1.0 == baseline"
" (whatever ``tech_fuel_price`` already implies). The multiplier sequence "
"MUST be non-decreasing for LP convexity."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:33
msgid ""
"Techs not listed in the CSV keep the v1.18 single-rate fuel cost "
"(``fuel_price * gen``). Mixing piecewise and flat-rate techs is fine."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:38
msgid "Constraints"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:40
msgid "Per ``(h, m, y, z, te)`` in the heat-rate set:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:42
msgid ""
"sum-to-gen: ``sum_s gen_segment[h, m, y, z, te, s] == gen[h, m, y, z, "
"te]``"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:44
msgid ""
"per-segment width: ``gen_segment[..., s] <= width[s] * cap_existing[y, z,"
" te] * dt``"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:47
msgid "where ``width[s] = frac_max[s] - frac_max[s-1]``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:49
msgid "Fuel cost replaces the flat ``fuel_price * gen`` with:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:51
msgid "``fuel_price[te, y] * sum_s multiplier[s] * gen_segment[..., s]``"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:53
msgid ""
"NPV-discounted via ``var_factor[y, z]`` and divided by ``weight``, "
"identical to the rest of ``cost_var``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:57
msgid "Config"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate:59
msgid ""
"``cost_parameters.is_piecewise_heat_rate`` (bool, default False). When "
"False, the module is a no-op and PREP-SHOT keeps the v1.18 flat-rate "
"behaviour byte-for-byte."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.AddHeatRateConstraints:1
msgid "Bases: :py:class:`object`"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.AddHeatRateConstraints:1
msgid "Piecewise-linear heat rate, opt-in."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.AddHeatRateConstraints
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.AddHeatRateConstraints.segment_width_rule:1
msgid "``gen_segment[s] <= (width[s] * cap_existing) * dt``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.AddHeatRateConstraints.segment_zero_rule:1
msgid "Force ``gen_segment[..., s] = 0`` for (te, s) not defined."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.AddHeatRateConstraints.sum_to_gen_rule:1
msgid "``sum_s gen_segment[..., s] == gen[h, m, y, z, te]``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.add_heat_rate_fuel_cost:1
msgid "Per-segment fuel cost contribution, NPV-discounted."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.add_heat_rate_fuel_cost:3
msgid "For each tech with a heat-rate curve, the fuel cost becomes:"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.add_heat_rate_fuel_cost:5
msgid "fuel_price[te, y] * sum_s multiplier[s] * gen_segment[..., s]"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.add_heat_rate_fuel_cost:7
msgid ""
"summed over (h, m, y, z), discounted by ``var_factor[y, z]``, and divided"
" by ``weight``. Returned as an ExprBuilder. Returns a zero ExprBuilder "
"when the module is disabled or no heat-rate curves are loaded."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.add_heat_rate_fuel_cost:12
msgid ""
"The CALLER (``cost.var_cost_rule``) must remove the corresponding techs' "
"contribution from the existing flat-rate ``fuel_cost_breakdown`` to avoid"
" double-counting -- handled by skipping those techs in the original "
"``fuel_cost_breakdown`` loop when ``hasattr(model, 'gen_segment')`` and "
"the tech is in ``segments_by_tech``."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.add_heat_rate_fuel_cost
#: prepshot._model.heat_rate.techs_with_heat_rate_curve
msgid "Return type"
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.techs_with_heat_rate_curve:1
msgid "Return the set of techs that have a heat-rate curve loaded."
msgstr ""

#: of prepshot._model.heat_rate.techs_with_heat_rate_curve:3
msgid ""
"Used by ``cost.fuel_cost_breakdown`` to skip techs that should be priced "
"through ``add_heat_rate_fuel_cost`` instead of the flat-rate fallback."
msgstr ""

